# Banking Contacts
A list of banking contacts saved in the database. Pending banking contacts will be displayed by default.

## Workflow:
A banking contact can have one of three different states that can be switched between by clicking on the corresponding buttons. These are displayed in the context menu if you right click the list row or at the top of the instance.

![Banking Contact Workflow](data:image/png;base64,)

_Displayed in red are those transitions that can only be administered by a manager._

### Draft:
The initial status after creating a new banking contact. After double checking your input you can submit the banking contact for review by a manager.

### Pending:
Pending banking contacts can either be approved or denied by a manager. Denying will transition its state back to draft where it can once again be modified and submitted.

### Approved:
The status after approval by a manager. From here you can edit it by transitioning its state back to "Draft".

## Columns:
Each column title has three lines on the right if you hover over it. Click on them to show options for that column. The second tab of the options menu will allow you to filter the column, the third to completely hide entire columns. Click on anywhere else on the column to order it, cycling between ascending, descending and no ordering. Hold shift while clicking to order multiple columns with individual weights.

### Location:
The contact's location of use. Can be one of four locations: Work, Private, Home or Other. Work will be selected by default when creating a new contact.

### Institute:
The name of the banking contact's institute.

### Institute additional:
Additional information about the institute, e.g. address.

### IBAN:
International Bank Account Number of the banking contact.

### SWIFT:
The contact's SWIFT code/BIC.

### Currency:
The bank's currency.

### Entry:
The entry for which this banking contact was created.

### Edited:
Date and time of last edit to the contact.

### Information:
Displays additional information that can be used instead of the IBAN to communicate banking details.

## Legend:
Click on the legend to filter banking contacts by status.

## Search Field:
Typing in the search field allows to filter the banking contacts by their institute, IBAN and SWIFT.
